<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-15T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-15T06:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 Struma Valley/6½: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Athens</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-15T13:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">February 15,
                                        1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 15—11:55
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Bids for Struma Valley reclamation called for March 9th. Greek Government
                            to telegraph specifications [to] its legations abroad today.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>